Task â„– 34

To do:
     Write the following SQL queries (Do not use MySQL):
a) There is an imaginary table Workers (id, name, hireDate (hire date), profession).
Retrieve all Testers from the Workers table, sorted by hire date.
b) Retrieve the last 5 hired Testers from the Workers table.


SOLUTION:

a) Retrieve all Testers from the Workers table, sorted by hire date.

SELECT * FROM Workers WHERE profession = 'QA' ORDER BY hireDate ASC;


b) Retrieve the last 5 hired Testers from the Workers table.

SELECT * FROM Workers WHERE profession = 'QA' ORDER BY hireDate DESC LIMIT 5;

